<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t think I=E2=80=99ve ever seen a=
 debt tender offer announced at 2 a.m.? You just fell asleep reading the wo=
rds =E2=80=9Cdebt tender offer,=E2=80=9D didn=E2=80=99t you? Nobody stays u=
p until the wee hours of the morning due to the excitement or urgency of a =
debt tender offer. But <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/30857809.259423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY3JlZGl0LXN1aXNzZS5jb20vYWJvdXQtdXMtbm=
V3cy9lbi9hcnRpY2xlcy9tZWRpYS1yZWxlYXNlcy9jc2ctYW5ub3VuY2VtZW50LTIwMjMwMy5od=
G1s/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB35a95cba" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> this</a> seems to have <a h=
ref=3D"bbg://news/stories/RRL8S7MB2SJR" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  hit the wire</a> at 1:45 =
a.m. Zurich time:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Credit Suisse Group takes decisive action to p=
re-emptively strengthen liquidity and announces public tender offers for de=
bt securities ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Credit Suisse is taking decisive action to pre=
-emptively strengthen its liquidity by intending to exercise its option to =
borrow from the Swiss National Bank (SNB) up to CHF 50 billion under a Cove=
red Loan Facility as well as a short-term liquidity facility, which are ful=
ly collateralized by high quality assets. Credit Suisse also announces offe=
rs by Credit Suisse International to repurchase certain OpCo senior debt se=
curities for cash of up to approximately CHF 3 billion.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Credit Suisse announces its intention to acces=
s the SNB=E2=80=99s Covered Loan Facility as well as a short-term liquidity=
 facility of up to approximately CHF 50 billion in aggregate. This addition=
al liquidity would support Credit Suisse=E2=80=99s core businesses and clie=
nts as Credit Suisse takes the necessary steps to create a simpler and more=
 focused bank built around client needs.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Credit Suisse also announces today that it is =
making a cash tender offer in relation to ten US dollar denominated senior =
debt securities for an aggregate consideration of up to USD 2.5 billion. Co=
ncurrently, Credit Suisse is also announcing a separate cash tender offer i=
n relation to four Euro denominated senior debt securities for an aggregate=
 consideration of up to EUR 500 million.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously the main point here is that the Swis=
s National Bank is giving Credit Suisse a 50 billion-Swiss-franc ($54 billi=
on) line of credit. One thing that this means is that, if depositors run on=
 Credit Suisse asking for their money back, Credit Suisse will have a lot o=
f money to give them.=C2=A0(As of its <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/30857809.259423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9peD9kb2M9L0F=
yY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMDAwMTE1OTUxMC8wMDAxMzcwMzY4MjMwMDAwMjYvY3MtMjAyMj=
EyMzEuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc1c9ee2b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsc=
ope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> 2022 annual report</=
a> it had CHF 234 billion of customer deposits, so the 50 billion from the =
SNB is a meaningful chunk.)</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another,=C2=A0more important thing that it mea=
ns is that the SNB is=C2=A0<em>willing=C2=A0</em>to give Credit Suisse the =
money, that it has talked to Credit Suisse management and looked at its boo=
ks and generally done its bank-regulatory work and said =E2=80=9Cehh, Credi=
t Suisse, still fine.=E2=80=9D The SNB and the Swiss Financial Market Super=
visory Authority <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3=
0857809.259423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc25iLmNoL2VuL21tci9yZWZlcmVuY2UvcHJlXzIwMjMw=
MzE1L3NvdXJjZS9wcmVfMjAyMzAzMTUuZW4ucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7d8bea84"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">put out a statement yesterday</a> saying that in so many words:</p=
>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Regulation in Switzerland requires all banks t=
o maintain capital and liquidity buffers that meet or exceed the minimum re=
quirements of the Basel standards. Furthermore, systemically important bank=
s have to meet higher capital and liquidity requirements. This allows negat=
ive effects of major crises and shocks to be absorbed.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Credit Suisse=E2=80=99s stock exchange value a=
nd the value of its debt securities have been particularly affected by mark=
et reactions in recent days. FINMA is in very close contact with the bank a=
nd has access to all information relevant to supervisory law. Against this =
background, FINMA confirms that Credit Suisse meets the higher capital and =
liquidity requirements applicable to systemically important banks. In addit=
ion, the SNB will provide liquidity to the globally active bank if necessar=
y.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A rough way to think about the dynamic of a gi=
ant bank failure is that the bank keeps going until its national regulator =
and central bank decide to pull the plug. Sometimes =E2=80=9Cpulling the pl=
ug=E2=80=9D means that the bank still has cash but the regulator says =E2=
=80=9Cyou=E2=80=99re done=E2=80=9D anyway,<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=
=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inli=
ne-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0while other times it means that the bank runs out of cash and=C2=
=A0calls its lender of last resort for more cash, and the lender of last re=
sort says no.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"colo=
r: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bor=
der-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background=
-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0The SNB/Finma statement, and Credit Suisse=C2=A0<em>actually draw=
ing CHF 50 billion</em>, is a way to reassure the market that the plug won=
=E2=80=99t get pulled anytime soon. The stock <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/30857809.259423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmN=
vbS9uZXdzL2xpdmUtYmxvZy8yMDIzLTAzLTE1L2NyZWRpdC1zdWlzc2UtaW4tY3Jpc2lzP2NtcG=
lkPUJCRDAzMTYyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzb=
GV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDMxNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8=
524a319a23cBe1688d4b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> rallied hard today</a>, though then it pared=
 gains when the European Central Bank <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/30857809.259423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXd=
zL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMTYvZWNiLWRlbGl2ZXJzLXBsYW5uZWQtaGFsZi1wb2ludC1oaW=
tlLWFzLWNyZWRpdC1zdWlzc2UtZmVhcnMtZWFzZT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMzE2MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGR=
iZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAzMTYm=
dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB83036341" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
  raised rates</a>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile, Credit Suisse=E2=80=99s=C2=A0<em>cr=
edit=C2=A0</em>instruments =E2=80=94=C2=A0its <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/30857809.259423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmN=
vbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMTUvY3JlZGl0LXN1aXNzZS1kb2xsYXItYm9uZHMtZH=
VlLTIwMjYtcGx1bmdlLXRvLWRpc3RyZXNzZWQtbGV2ZWxzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAzMTYyM19NT05FW=
VNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIz=
MDMxNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcd649e8c" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
