or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #=
ccc;"> had deposit outflows</a> in recent months), but in the sense that th=
ey get more of their money from short-term capital-markets lenders and deri=
vatives counterparties, and=C2=A0<em>those=C2=A0</em>investors =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0banks, hedge funds, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0<em>are </em>uninsured, quick-mo=
ving, well-informed, herd-like and rates-sensitive, and when they flee then=
 that=E2=80=99s a crisis. Banks and hedge funds follow financial news close=
ly and tend to be jumpy in times of stress, and they seem nervous about len=
ding to Credit Suisse.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the SNB is not.=C2=A0And so there is a tra=
de.=C2=A0Here is the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/30857809.259423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzEx=
